history.content:
My name is Alex, and I’m here to tell you guys about Cal Hacks, one of the largest collegiate hackathons hosted at our very own Cal Memorial Stadium! Cal Hacks is a weekend to kick back with your friends for a weekend of coding, workshops, and fun! It’s a great place to pick up some new skills, meet people with similar interests, and enjoy yourself! Plenty more information, as well as the application portal, can be found at calhacks.io.

 

Cal Hacks also relies heavily on volunteers to shape the event. If you’re interested in checking out how a hackathon operates or meeting some of the organizers of the event, we would greatly appreciate if you volunteered! Volunteer signups are available on the website as well. 


If you have any questions or concerns, feel free to reach out to team@calhacks.io. Hope to see you there!
history.subject: Cal Hacks 6.0!!
